<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="520" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d520">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.857 Su 8/81½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">17 April, 1916</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Circumstances of this
                            sort are of course very disturbing;<note n="40" xml:id="d520fn1">See
                                letter from The Secretary of State to President Wilson, Apr. 15,
                                1916, p. 548.</note> but I did not know that we had learned the name
                            of the submarine which attacked the <hi rend="italic">Sussex</hi>.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>